  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1507970/extras/93600a03cb6ef3de10dad90a236a75ba.poster.avif?t=1734721449\" width=600 height=400 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1507970/extras/93600a03cb6ef3de10dad90a236a75ba.webm?t=1734721449\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1507970/extras/93600a03cb6ef3de10dad90a236a75ba.mp4?t=1734721449\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br><br>Word game is literally a game of words. <br><br>Words are not only composing narratives and interfaces, but also representing objects, characters and scenes.<br><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1507970/extras/b45e124caddf21716d0e605f859758b8.poster.avif?t=1734721449\" width=600 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1507970/extras/b45e124caddf21716d0e605f859758b8.webm?t=1734721449\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1507970/extras/b45e124caddf21716d0e605f859758b8.mp4?t=1734721449\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br><br>Player controls \"I\" to challenge puzzles composed of words.<br><br>When \"I\" appears a secret room, in-game narrative clearly tells \"I\" that \"there is no door”. However, in the world of word game, “I\" can walk through the \"door” because there is a “door”.<br><br>“I\" should find clues between lines, delete words to change the meaning of sentences, or shift words to rewrite facts. “I” must be wise and brave enough complete the mission of words.<br><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop play